# config/yards/example.env — TEMPLATE for a named-yard definition. Copy it to a REGISTRY
# location (this file itself is never loaded — it only documents the shape):
#
#   private/yards/<name>.env               operator overlay (private repo), takes precedence
#   ~/.config/subyard/yards/<name>.env     machine-local (no private repo)
#
# The file name IS the yard name: private/yards/openclaw.env → `yard -Y openclaw …` (or the
# sugar `yard @openclaw …`). Names must match [a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]* (lowercase, digits, - _).
#
# A yard context is just an env layer sourced FIRST, before config/*.env, so anything you set
# here wins over the generic defaults. Everything Subyard derives from the yard name — the
# instance (yard-<name>), the Incus project (subyard-<name>), the ssh alias (yard-<name>), the
# /srv volume (yard-srv-<name>), the personal-data mount root (/srv/subyard-<name> ⇒ HOST_BASE)
# and the machine-local project state — so you normally only NEED to set SSH_PORT. Put per-yard
# values here; keep global operator settings in private/config.env (it loads LAST and can still
# clobber, so do not repeat global values per yard).

# REQUIRED — the host loopback port for this yard's ssh proxy device. It is the ONE thing
# Subyard cannot derive without risking a collision with another yard. Give every yard a
# unique free port; `yard check` / `yard init` flag a duplicate (init refuses).
SSH_PORT=2223

# --- optional -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Restrict this yard to specific profiles (space-separated). Empty/unset = all profiles (the
# default-yard behavior). When set, `yard provision` with no argument provisions exactly these,
# and `yard status` lists only these profiles' shared resources.
# YARD_PROFILES="openclaw"

# Run this yard as a VM instead of a system container (stronger boundary, clean nesting).
# INSTANCE_TYPE=vm

# Resource limits for this yard's instance.
# LIMITS_CPU=8
# LIMITS_MEMORY=24GiB

# Coding agents to lay default configs for in this yard (see config/agents.env).
# AGENTS="claude codex pi"

# Any other config/*.env key may be overridden per yard, e.g. a bespoke host-mount set:
# HOST_MOUNTS="
# host-secrets:/mnt/host/secrets:ro:0700
# host-memory:/mnt/host/memory:rw:0770
# "
